# Supabase project credentials. Copy to .env.local and fill in real values.
# The anon key is safe to ship client-side; security is enforced by RLS
# (see supabase/migrations), not key secrecy.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
# Astroverse: Constellation Nexus — environment configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (which is git-ignored) and fill in the
# values for your Supabase project:
#
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#
# Both variables are read by the Vite client at build/dev time
# (see supabaseClient.ts). The anon key is safe to ship in client code by
# design — Supabase's security boundary is Row Level Security evaluated by
# Postgres against auth.uid(), not secrecy of this key. Never put the
# service_role key here or anywhere in client-bundled code.

# Project URL — Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API → Project URL
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://dbxrywnlrogaxlytwriv.supabase.co

# Anon/public key — Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API → Project API keys → anon public
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key-here
